{"index": 771, "title": "Senior Software Engineer", "job_location": "Baltimore, MD", "jd_text": "ForgeOS is hiring a Senior Software Engineer to join a growing team of developers to work on the ForgeOS product.\u00a0Become a valued member of the software team where your expertise will be recognized and your contributions celebrated as we build cutting-edge solutions in the telecom space.The Senior Software Engineer has ownership of complex, mission-critical features from concept to production. This position helps to define how we build, not just what we build. This role acts as a force multiplier for the team by writing high-leverage code, mentoring junior engineers, and championing best practices in scalability, security, and AI-assisted development. This role can transition into a manager position in addition to other growth opportunities.At ForgeOS, our mission is to develop and deliver the technology, tools, talent, and insight required to make a demonstrable positive impact on the bottom line for telecom partners and their customers. With over 50 years of collective technology, partner channel, and industry experience, ForgeOS delivers automation and expertise designed to unravel the complexity of the telecom market.ForgeOS offers a great benefits package including 3 weeks of paid Vacation, 1 week of paid Sick time, 10 paid company holidays as well as an extra day of PTO to use on your birthday! Professional development budget, 401(k), mentoring programs and many more benefits are available at ForgeOS \u2013 apply today to see what working for an industry disrupter can do for your career. www.forgeos.coThis is a hybrid role working from our Baltimore, MD office approximately 3-4 times per month. The starting salary for this position is $110k - $130k per year.JOB TITLE: Senior Software EngineerREPORTS TO: Engineering ManagerESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:\u00a0Lead the design and implementation of complex full-stack features, modules, and systems with minimal supervision. A \u201csystem\u201d means the full vertical \u2014 frontend, API, database, deployment, and tests \u2014 not just backend. You are trusted with the hardest problems.Design scalable, resilient services and data layers across the stack, ensuring they meet performance and security standards.Proactively identify technical debt and lead refactoring initiatives to modernize legacy systems into service-oriented architectures.Build systems with \u201cradical observability\u201d in mind \u2014 ensuring logs, metrics, and error handling provide clear evidence of system health. No silent failures.Conduct thorough code reviews and provide technical guidance to Software Engineers and Juniors, fostering a culture of excellence and growth.Partner directly with Product and Design to translate business goals into technical specifications that prioritize user value.Contribute to architectural decisions and advocate for patterns that improve the team\u2019s long-term velocity.Architect features for AI collaboration \u2014 clean separation of concerns, well-documented interfaces, modular design that AI can reason about and extend.Leverage AI as a collaborative technical partner for generating architectural scaffolding, writing tests, and exploring design alternatives.Establish patterns that make the codebase more AI-readable and AI-maintainable over time.QUALIFICATIONS:\u00a0\u00a0Bachelor\u2019s degree in Computer Science required or equivalent experience. We value demonstrated ability and shipped projects over credentials.5+ years of professional software development experience, or equivalent demonstrated impact.\u00a0Strong architectural skills \u2014 ability to design systems, not just features. You think in services, data flows, and failure modes.Proficiency across multiple languages (Python, MySQL, laravel, Vue.js, etc.) frameworks, and paradigms. We don\u2019t require specific technologies \u2014 we require the judgment to choose the right tool for the problem