{"index": 815, "title": "Backend Engineer (node.js) - Leaply", "job_location": "Warsaw, Mazowieckie, Poland", "jd_text": "Hello! We are Leaply - an ecosystem of interconnected digital and physical products designed to help people build healthy habits and improve quality of life. We\u2019re building a portfolio of B2C products for global markets, including the US, Tier-1 countries, Europe, and beyond. In June 2024 we launched a new web platform for habit-building with a subscription model and performance-first marketing across Meta, Google, and TikTok.We started as a startup in 2024 and grew 10\u00d7 in the last six months. In 2025, we\u2019re aiming for another 5\u00d7. Demand is validated, and the user flow is steady. Next up: a mobile app that rethinks how habits are formed.At Leaply, we challenge traditional career paths - we value ownership over titles and impact over process. We move fast, think big, and expect everyone to contribute beyond their scope to build the next Ukrainian unicorn.To deliver on this vision, we\u2019re hiring a Backend Engineer (Node.js) who will act as a founding engineer for our Payments & Operations zone. This is not just about \"integration\" \u2014 you will build the financial backbone of the company that handles 5x growth, ensuring scalability, reliability, and automation across our revenue streams.What You\u2019ll Do\u2014 Act as a cross-functional partner: Work directly with Payment, Marketing, and Ops teams to translate business goals into technical solutions that drive revenue;\u2014 Own the Payments Domain: Design and build resilient payment infrastructure (Node.js/NestJS), ensuring transactional integrity, smart retries, and accurate financial data synchronization;\u2014 Infrastructure & DevOps: Take full ownership of your services' lifecycle \u2014 from architectural design to deployment and monitoring in our cloud environment (GCP, Kubernetes, Terraform); \u2014 Data & Analytics: Build reliable data pipelines (BigQuery) to empower analytics and ensure every cent is accounted for;\u2014 Collaborate, don't isolate: While you lead the Payments zone, you\u2019ll work closely with the wider Engineering Chapter, sharing knowledge and building the platform together;\u2014 (Nice to have) Contribute to simple internal tools or dashboards (React/Next.js) to unblock Ops teams when needed.What Matters To Us\u2014 3+ years of commercial experience building scalable web backends;\u2014 Expert with Node.js (NestJS preferred) and TypeScript;\u2014 Strong experience with PostgreSQL (transactions, isolation levels) and asynchronous architectures (Queues, Event-driven);\u2014 Hands-on DevOps experience: You are comfortable setting up CI/CD, configuring Docker, and managing resources in Kubernetes/GCP;\u2014 Revenue-driven mindset: You understand that \"code quality\" means \"business reliability\". You care about metrics like Payment Success Rate as much as CPU Load;\u2014 Proactive communication: You don't wait for tasks \u2014 you identify problems and propose technical solutions to business challenges;\u2014 You use AI in your workflow to move faster and think broader.Bonus points\u2014 Experience in FinTech, E-commerce, or High-load projects;\u2014 Deep understanding of Payment Processing (Idempotency, Reconciliation, Fraud prevention);\u2014 Experience with Data Engineering (BigQuery, ETL pipelines);\u2014 Familiarity with Infrastructure as Code (Terraform);\u2014 Willingness to occasionally touch Front-end (React) to build internal tools.What You Can Expect\u2014 Competitive compensation;\u2014 Founding Engineer Impact: You will be the architect of a critical business zone with high autonomy, but surrounded by a strong engineering ecosystem;\u2014 No Legacy Bureaucracy: We are young, fast, and you will set the standards for processes and code quality;\u2014 Strong Community: Regular knowledge-sharing sessions with engineers across Skelar (10+ successful businesses);\u2014 Office in Warsaw or Kyiv with generator/Starlink, plus perks (lunches, gym, health insurance);\u2014 A meaningful mission - helping people live better lives, every day.Leaply is backed by SKELAR, a venture builder with 10+ successful B2C businesses in its portfolio. SKELAR provides world-class payment infrastructure for our model, plus financial and legal support across target regions, and runs internal clubs focused on professional growth in marketing, engineering, and payments - there\u2019s always someone to learn from or lean on.Beyond business, SKELAR supports the SKELAR Foundation, a charitable initiative created by employees to support the Ukrainian Armed Forces - funding large projects that bring us closer to victory.Join us and help build the next big everything!\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "Warsaw, Mazowieckie, Poland", "loc": "OUTSIDE_UK", "arr_raw": null, "arr": "UNK", "sen_raw": "Backend Engineer (Node.js) who will act as a founding engineer", "sen": "LEVEL_3", "tech_raw": "Node.js, NestJS, TypeScript, PostgreSQL, Kubernetes, Terraform, BigQuery, React, Next.js, AI", "tech": ["NODE", "JS_TS", "REACT"], "comp_raw": null, "comp": "NO_GBP"}}
